Subject: [PATCH] Skip setup_requires
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

m2r is needed just for readme generation.
setuptools-scm is needed to set version but lets just use version
argument.

Signed-off-by: Tomi Lepp√§nen <tomi.leppanen@jolla.com>
---
 setup.py | 4 +---
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/setup.py b/setup.py
index 3fb7fdb..37a00f9 100644
--- a/setup.py
+++ b/setup.py
@@ -14,7 +14,7 @@ except(IOError, ImportError):
 
 setup(
     name='Automat',
-    use_scm_version=True,
+    version='VERSION',
     url='https://github.com/glyph/Automat',
     description="""
     Self-service finite-state machines for the programmer on the go.
@@ -23,8 +23,6 @@ setup(
     packages=find_packages(exclude=[]),
     package_dir={'automat': 'automat'},
     setup_requires=[
-        'setuptools-scm',
-        'm2r',
     ],
     install_requires=[
         "attrs>=19.2.0",
